The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 FDI to be encouraged

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, May 24: The government will encourage foreign direct investment (FDI) and joint ventures in diamond exploration, mining, cutting, polishing and marketing. 

 Union commerce minister Kamal Nath said the government was also keen to encourage investment by Indians in diamond mines abroad.

 There has to be an assured supply of rough diamonds for the industry to grow. There is a need for Indian investors to invest in foreign mines and the government is considering allowing such investments, he said while pointing out that enormous opportunities exist not only for FDI by foreigners in India, but also for local industrialists in other countries.




